contract "CON-2026-217" {
  title = "Gradient cache: multi-dimensional incremental invalidation"
  status = "complete"
  created_at = 2026-03-05T20:57:45Z
  updated_at = 2026-03-05T20:57:45Z
  goal = "Every mos vcs commit is a displacement vector in a multi-dimensional quality state space. The gradient cache captures, stores, and exploits this structure. Phase 0: on each commit, snapshot the governance state (lint errors, test pass rate, coverage, drift count, structural metrics, harness results) as .mos/vcs/snapshots/<hash>.json. Phase 1: file-level mtime/SHA256 cache for incremental parsing. Phase 2: dimension-aware invalidation (map lint rules to artifact fields, skip unaffected axes). Phase 3: scalability harness with synthetic profiles. The snapshot series enables velocity computation, convergence detection, and trajectory analysis -- turning commit history into a navigable vector field toward the desired state."
  kind = "feature"

  section "phases" {
    text = """
Phase 0 (commit state snapshot): on each mos vcs commit, run a lightweight governance scan and store the result as .mos/vcs/snapshots/<commit-hash>.json. The snapshot captures: lint_errors (int), lint_warnings (int), scenarios_total (int), scenarios_passing (int), drift_violations (int), harness_pass_count (int), harness_fail_count (int), structural_metrics (map of metric name to value), integrity_index (float 0-100). This is the position vector at commit time. The displacement vector between consecutive snapshots is computed by subtraction.

Phase 1 (cache index): .mos/cache/index.json with path -> mtime + SHA256 + extracted fields. On lint/status/harness, stat files first, skip parse if unchanged. Expected impact: common case (nothing changed) drops to near-zero I/O.

Phase 2 (gradient vectors): map each lint rule to the artifact fields it reads. On change, compute which axes (lint, coverage, traceability, sprint) have non-zero deltas. Only re-evaluate rules on affected axes. Sum vectors for batched changes.

Phase 3 (scalability harness): synthetic project generator at 100/1K/10K/50K artifacts. Benchmark mos lint, mos status, mos fmt with ceiling thresholds. Regression detection across runs."""
  }

  section "conceptual-model" {
    text = """
Commits as vectors: all code evolution is movement from current state to desired state. Each commit is a displacement vector V where V[axis] = snapshot(n+1)[axis] - snapshot(n)[axis]. The commit history is a discrete trajectory through governance state space. The harness defines the feasible region: thresholds (ceilings and floors) form a convex constraint surface. Pre-commit gates reject any commit whose displacement would land outside this region. For AI agents, the rejected displacement is a feedback signal: recalculate the step to stay within bounds.

Velocity = rate of change of distance-to-goal per unit (commit, day, sprint). Positive convergence velocity means the project is approaching the desired state. Near-zero velocity = stall. Oscillating sign = churn. This vocabulary (goal, position, velocity, trajectory, feasible region) unifies the gradient cache, integrity index, drift tracking, and three-vectors quality system into one coherent model."""
  }
  depends_on = "CON-2026-218"
  slug = "gradient-cache"
}

